cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with improving the signal strength, rate, and BER of full-duplex radios, which are related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the design of full-duplex radios, which are used in wireless networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes an analog baseband cancellation technique to improve the performance of full-duplex radios, which can be seen as a control system. 
4. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper discusses the design of radios, which can be considered as a hardware architecture problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with improving the signal strength and rate of radios, which can be related to multimedia applications such as video streaming.
